cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

The paper focuses on using convolutional neural networks (ConvNets or CNNs) for remote sensing scene classification, which is a computer vision problem. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses different strategies for using existing ConvNets, which involves machine learning techniques such as fine-tuning and feature extraction, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The paper also mentions the use of linear SVM, which is a popular classification algorithm in machine learning, further supporting the likelihood of cs.LG. The paper also involves the use of deep learning techniques, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves information retrieval techniques, such as feature extraction, which falls under cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper involves optimization techniques, such as finding the best performing strategy, which falls under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
